-- 
Moscow May Scrap Third of Luzkhov’s Projects, RBC Daily Reports

-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 
2011-02-25T05:55:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/moscow-may-scrap-third-of-luzkhov-s-projects-rbc-daily-reports.html
Moscow Mayor  Sergei Sobyanin  may
scrap more than a third of new building projects approved by his
predecessor Yury Luzhkov, RBC Daily reported, citing official
documents.  Sobyanin, a former chief of staff of Prime Minister
Vladimir Putin who became mayor after Luzkhov’s sacking in
September, plans to annul permission for about 500 construction
projects, the Moscow-based newspaper said. Companies affected
include Mirax Group, M.O.R.E.-Plaza and Engeocom, RBC Daily
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henry Meyer in Moscow at 
 hmeyer4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at   wmorris@bloomberg.net . 